    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-02T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="479"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-02T12:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 2, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 2—6:05
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>597. With reference to the third paragraph of the Chinese Foreign Minister’s
                    statement quoted in my 595, December 1, 10 a.m.,<note n="98" xml:id="d479fn98">
                        <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_122">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 122</ref>.</note> he orally informed me
                    yesterday that representatives in Chungking of third powers according
                    recognition to the Nanking regime would be handed their passports.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department. Repeated to Peiping for transmission by air mail to
                    Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
